## Proposed Changes

### Database Layer

#### [NEW] `peer_review_migration.sql`

SQL migration file to run in Supabase SQL Editor. Creates:

**`peer_reviews` table:**
| Column | Type | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `id` | uuid PK | Unique review ID |
| `node_id` | uuid FK → nodes | Which node was reviewed |
| `reviewer_id` | uuid FK → profiles | Who reviewed it |
| `target_tier` | text | Which tier is being assessed for |
| `overall_recommendation` | text | `meets_standard` / `needs_work` / `not_ready` |
| `confidence` | text | `high` / `medium` / `low` |
| `overall_comment` | text | Open-ended comment (where the best signal lives) |
| `criteria_scores` | jsonb | `{ criterion_key: { score: 1-5, comment?: string } }` |
| `cycle_id` | uuid FK → review_cycles | Groups reviews into cycles |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | When submitted |

**`review_cycles` table:**
| Column | Type | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `id` | uuid PK | Cycle identifier |
| `node_id` | uuid FK → nodes | Which node |
| `target_tier` | text | Tier being assessed for |
| `initiated_by` | uuid FK → profiles | Who started the review |
| `status` | text | `open` / `closed` / `consensus` / `split` |
| `min_reviews` | int | Minimum reviews to close (default 3) |
| `result_tier` | text | Final tier after cycle closes (null while open) |
| `result_summary` | text | Generated summary of review consensus |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | Cycle opened |
| `closed_at` | timestamptz | Cycle closed |

**RPC `submit_peer_review`** — SECURITY DEFINER function that:
1. Inserts review into `peer_reviews`
2. Checks if the cycle has enough reviews to auto-close
3. If so, calculates consensus and updates cycle status
4. Awards reputation to reviewer

**RLS Policies:**
- Everyone can read reviews (radical transparency)
- Reviews cannot be read by other reviewers while cycle is `open` (prevents anchoring)
- Authenticated users can insert reviews

