## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Who can initiate a review cycle?** The plan currently allows L3+ for b_class+ and L2+ for lower tiers. Should anyone be able to nominate a node for review, or only contributors or group members?

> [!NOTE]
> **Self-nomination**: Should the contributor who wrote the content be able to nominate their own node for review? The research doesn't address this directly. My recommendation: yes, allow it — the rubric and independence requirements handle the objectivity concern.

